## When to use this component

Use the Breadcrumbs component when you need to help users orientate themselves within websites with multiple levels.

### When not to use this component

Don’t use the Breadcrumbs component on websites with a flat structure, or to show progress through a linear journey or transaction.

If you’re using other navigational devices on the page, such as a sidebar, consider whether your users need the additional support of breadcrumbs.

## How it works

The Breadcrumbs component should include the user’s current page, which should be visually different from the other pages linked to in the breadcrumb.

There are two ways to use the Breadcrumbs component. You can use HTML or, if you are using [Nunjucks](https://mozilla.github.io/nunjucks/) or the [GOV.UK Prototype Kit](https://govuk-prototype-kit.herokuapp.com/docs), you can use the Breadcrumbs macro.
