# Breadcrumb

## Introduction

The Breadcrumb component helps users to understand where they are within a website and move between levels.

[Preview the Breadcrumb component](http://govuk-frontend-review.herokuapp.com/components/breadcrumb).

Read guidance on when to use the Breadcrumb component in your service in the [GOV.UK Design System](https://govuk-design-system-prototypes.cloudapps.digital/design-patterns/patterns/components/breadcrumbs/).

## Dependencies

You must be running [npm version 5 or above](http://blog.npmjs.org/post/161081169345/v500) to use the Breadcrumb component.

The Breadcrumb component depends on @govuk-frontend/globals and @govuk-frontend/icons, which will be automatically installed with the package.

## Installation

Install the Breadcrumb component by running the command:

	npm install --save @govuk-frontend/breadcrumb

## Configuration

To use the Breadcrumb component you need to setup your build tool to find the package in the node_modules.

When compiling the Sass files you’ll need to define includePaths to reference the node_modules directory.

Below is a sample configuration using Gulp js:

	.pipe(sass({ includePaths: 'node_modules/' }))

### Static asset path configuration

To show the Breadcrumb image you need to configure your app. Use the sample configuration in Express js to do this:

	app.use('/public', express.static(path.join(__dirname, '/node_modules/@govuk-frontend/icons')))

	app.use('/public', express.static(path.join(__dirname, '/node_modules/@govuk-frontend/icons')))


